data.description: This home sits on 7.88 acres of land and has 5 outbuildings! The home itself has a unique story that could take you back in time! The front half of the home was built in 1790 and the back half of the home was built in 1840 however, it was brought to the property and connected via the kitchen and catwalk in 1980. There is a whole article in ''The Architectural History of Jones County'' also known as the '' Scott-Miller House'' and is super interesting. The kitchen cabinets are made from reclaimed wood from the existing structures and are a beautiful touch to the kitchen!  This home also features a screened in back porch and a very spacious covered front porch. The barns can be used for livestock or horses. The owners were homesteaders and gardened vegetables ,raised pigs, goats, cows, sheep, chickens and even ducks!  The property has several fruit trees scattered around as well.   The metal roof and HVAC unit were installed in October of 2020.  This home is unique and if you have questions, contact me or your agent !
